What is Linux?
Linux is an open-source operating system kernel created by Linus Torvalds in 1991. It acts as an interface between hardware and software.

Why Linux for DevOps?
Most cloud servers run Linux
Docker containers run on Linux
Kubernetes worker nodes run Linux
Jenkins servers commonly run Linux
Automation tools work best on Linux

